  <summary date="2004-07-13T19:15:17Z" status="Introduced in House">Policyholder Disaster Protection Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow insurance companies (other than life insurance companies) to make tax deductible contributions to a tax-exempt policyholder disaster protection fund established by this Act for the payment of policyholders' claims arising from certain catastrophic events, such as windstorms, earthquakes, fires, or floods.</summary>
